libcitygml
------------------------------------------
CityGML (City Geography Markup Language) is an XML-based schema for the
modelling and exchange of georeferenced 3D city and landscape models that is
quickly being adopted on an international level.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.11.2-1
  libcitygml-devel-2.1.0-1bl1
  libcitygml2-2.1.0-1bl1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libgdal20-2.4.0-1
  libGLU-devel-9.0.0-1
  libGLU1-9.0.0-1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  libxerces-c31-3.1.4-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.4-2
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.31.2-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  ninja-1.8.2-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/jklimke/libcitygml

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/jklimke/libcitygml/archive/2.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libcitygml-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libcitygml-2.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libcitygml-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcitygml-2.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcitygml2-2.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcitygml-devel-2.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

